Very sneaky way of charging customers. The food was good so I won't lower the rating of this 'popular' location but everyone should be aware -- they have an ALL DAY SPECIAL pricing which gives you an egg roll and drink with most meals, BUT, if you don't ask for the special, they will not give it to you and will charge you a higher price. What's the point of having a ALL DAY special if you're going to charge a higher price unless someone asks for it. The worker even went as far as telling me that it's like if you go to a store and don't ask for the sale price, they will charge you full price. I'm sorry but any where I go shopping, if something's on sale, the sale price shows up automatically. I'm sure many customers do not know about this but should be made aware. Don't hustle your customers like that with sleezy pricing. They did give me the difference back, but if I didnt say something, I wouldnt of gotten anything.

We recently visited NYC with one of our children in order to get them set up in the City for their first year of college.  My wife booked a great little airbnb close to the Barclay Center.  Our last night in town was pretty quiet, after a long day and incredibly long weekend.  We knew that we would be saying goodbye to our child for the foreseeable future so we just wanted to order in and relax at the airbnb.  After searing google for a few minutes, No Pork Halal popped up.  So, we gave it at try.  We placed an order, walked to the store front (no, minimal seating - pretty much pick-up only), paid and grabbed our meal in less than 30 minutes (including walking time).  For the price, the meal was excellent. The service was friendly, prompt, and attentive.  The place was packed with people (always a good sign) picking up to go orders.  So, if you're looking to feed your family at a reasonable price and you love quick-pick Chinese food, then this is your place.  If you want pork fried rice, however, you're out of luck.  We went for the chicken and were satisfied!
